git 

Set up a new Master repository to github and upload local files:
cd `current repository`
git init
git add .
git commit -m "First commit"
git remote add orgin https://github.com/prairie-guy/gpu_setup.git
git push -u origin master

# Files to be ignored belong in .gitignore file

# To clone from Master to a new client
git clone https://github.com/prairie-guy/euler.git

# To sycn local client with Master
git pull

# After changes:
git status              # Status of tree
git add .               # Stage all files for updating (Only specific files: git add `files` )
git commit -m "Changes" # Commit changed files
git push                # Push files to github


